{"id":36045,"title":"[Current clinical description of adult atopic dermatitis patients].","abstract":"With regards to big number of atopic dermatitis patients we performed analysis of medical history and clinical signs of adult atopic dermatitis patients under the in-patient treatment and at early follow-up period. Typical occurrence of medical and personal history was shown. Lichenoid and erythematous-squamous with lichenification occurrence of the disease were dominant. 55% cases of aggravation were accompanied by sympathicotonia, 21% cases by secondary bacterial skin infections. Majority of patients have signs of the disease at discharge. 18% patients have signs of worsening during 1 months of follow-up. 28% patients only are expected to cooperate with medical staff in effective manner due to special way of disease cooping.","date":"2014-03-10","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24605639","annotations":[{"name":"Cutaneous conditions","weight":0.906986,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cutaneous_conditions"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.841915,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Medical history","weight":0.815845,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_history"},{"name":"Bacteria","weight":0.804197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacteria"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Skin","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.683991,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Medical sign","weight":0.545489,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_sign"},{"name":"Adult","weight":0.52712,"wikipedia_article":"http://en